{"article_id":"LcReqRpzXSqUBpol","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Snowden took Booz Allen job","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"to get NSA secrets ,","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"Hong Kong paper reports","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"Snowden seeks refuge in Ecuador","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"and was last reported in Moscow","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"Washington says","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"Snowden is a wanted man ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"urges nations to turn him away","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"Pleading for asylum","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"after spilling American secrets ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"Edward Snowden told Ecuador 's government","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"that he fears inhumane treatment or even death","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"if he 's handed over","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"to face U.S. espionage charges ,","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"Ecuador 's foreign minister said Monday .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"Snowden told Ecuadorian President Rafael Correa","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"that it is `` unlikely that I will have a fair trial or humane treatment ''","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"if handed over to U.S. officials","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"to stand trial ,","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"according to a letter from Snowden","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"read by Foreign Minister Ricardo Patino .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"The whereabouts of Snowden , the computer contractor","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"who exposed details of the National Security Agency 's surveillance programs ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"were uncertain late Monday .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"He was last known to be in Moscow ,","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"where he landed after a flight from Hong Kong on Sunday .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"He had been expected to board a flight to Cuba on Monday ,","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"Russia 's semiofficial Interfax news agency reported .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"But CNN journalists on two successive Moscow-to-Havana flights said","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"Snowden did not appear to be in the cabin ,","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"while officials at the Russian capital 's Sheremetyevo International Airport declined to say","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"whether he was still there .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"JUST WATCHED Snowden : Intel value vs . Politics","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"MUST WATCH Snowden : Intel value vs . Politics","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"02:16","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"JUST WATCHED Where is NSA leaker Edward Snowden ?","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"MUST WATCH Where is NSA leaker Edward Snowden ?","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"02:35","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"JUST WATCHED Dershowitz :","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"Greenwald 's a total phony","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"MUST WATCH Dershowitz :","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"Greenwald 's a total phony","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"02:36","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"JUST WATCHED Giuliani :","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Snowden 's chance of conviction","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"MUST WATCH Giuliani :","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"Snowden 's chance of conviction","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"01:39","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"U.S. officials have yanked Snowden 's passport ,","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"but he left Hong Kong on a `` refugee document of passage ''","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"issued by Ecuador ,","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"according to Julian Assange , founder of the anti-secrecy group WikiLeaks ,","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"which is aiding Snowden 's efforts","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"to find a safe haven .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"Assange would say only","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"that the former National Security Agency contractor is `` in a safe place","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"and his spirits are high . ''","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"While Patino ,","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"speaking at a news conference in Vietnam ,","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"the country has yet to decide on Snowden 's asylum request ,","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"he questioned","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"whether it was Snowden or the United States that was acting badly in the affair .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"He called the surveillance programs","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"revealed by Snowden","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"`` a breach of the rights '' of people around the world .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"`` We have to ask ,","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"who has betrayed who ? ''","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"Correa , meanwhile , took to Twitter","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"to address the issue .","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"`` Rest assured","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"that we will analyze the Snowden case very responsibly","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"and we will make with absolute sovereignty the decision","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"that we believe","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"is most appropriate , ''","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"the president tweeted .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"He added ,","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"`` A big hug to everyone and happy week . ''","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"Snowden has acknowledged","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"that he leaked classified documents about NSA-run surveillance programs to the Guardian newspaper in Britain and to The Washington Post .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"The documents revealed the existence of programs","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"that collect records of domestic telephone calls in the United States","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"and monitor the Internet activity of overseas residents .","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"The disclosures shook the U.S. intelligence community","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"and raised questions","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"about whether the NSA is eroding American civil liberties .","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"He walked away from a six-figure job in Hawaii with the computer consulting firm Booz Allen Hamilton , an NSA contractor ,","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"and went to Hong Kong","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"before the newspapers began publishing stories","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"based on his leak .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"He told the Guardian","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"that he exposed the surveillance programs","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"because they pose a threat to democracy ,","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"but administration officials said","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"the programs are vital","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"to preventing terrorist attacks","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"and are overseen by all three branches of government .","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"A Hong Kong paper , the South China Morning Post , reported Tuesday","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"that Snowden took the job at Booz Allen early this year","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"to `` collect proof '' about the programs","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"before disclosing them to reporters .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"Snowden told the paper","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"that he intends to release more of the documents","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"he took from the firm .","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"`` If I have time","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"to go through this information ,","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"I would like to make it available to journalists in each country","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"to make their own assessment , independent of my bias ,","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"as to whether or not the knowledge of U.S. network operations against their people should be published , ''","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"the newspaper quoted Snowden","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"as saying .","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"In addition to Ecuador , Snowden is asking Iceland and other , unspecified countries to consider granting him asylum ,","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"WikiLeaks attorney Michael Ratner told reporters Friday .","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"Snowden tests U.S. relationships","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"MUST WATCH Snowden tests U.S. relationships","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"04:19","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"We want to know :","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"Where 's Ed ?","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"We want to know :","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"Where 's Ed ?","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"02:28","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"WikiLeaks spokesman :","depth":15},{"id":134,"text":"I know where he is","depth":15},{"id":135,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":14},{"id":136,"text":"MUST WATCH WikiLeaks spokesman :","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"I know where he is","depth":15},{"id":138,"text":"02:23","depth":14},{"id":139,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"Did the U.S. drop the ball on Snowden ?","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"Did the U.S. drop the ball on Snowden ?","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"02:00","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"Iceland has not received a formal application from Snowden ,","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"the Interior Ministry said Monday .","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"Meanwhile , U.S. officials cast a wide net","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"seeking his return ,","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"telling Russia and Latin American countries","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"that they should hand Snowden over","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"should he land on their soil .","depth":14},{"id":152,"text":"President Barack Obama told reporters Monday","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"that the United States is pursuing all legal channels","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"to bring Snowden back .","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"And White House spokesman Jay Carney said","depth":13},{"id":156,"text":"U.S. officials are reaching out to numerous countries in an effort","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"to have Snowden turned over .","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"`` The U.S. is advising these governments","depth":14},{"id":159,"text":"that Mr. Snowden is wanted on felony charges","depth":15},{"id":160,"text":"and as such should not be allowed to proceed in any further international travel","depth":16},{"id":161,"text":"other than is necessary","depth":17},{"id":162,"text":"to return him here to the United States , ''","depth":17},{"id":163,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"But CNN legal analyst Jeffrey Toobin said","depth":16},{"id":165,"text":"the issue now `` is much more of a political and diplomatic matter","depth":17},{"id":166,"text":"than it is a legal matter . ''","depth":17},{"id":167,"text":"`` In an ordinary case , sure , you need a passport","depth":17},{"id":168,"text":"to get around , ''","depth":17},{"id":169,"text":"Toobin said .","depth":16},{"id":170,"text":"`` But here ,","depth":16},{"id":171,"text":"where this case is causing increasing embarrassment for the United States ,","depth":16},{"id":172,"text":"governments","depth":17},{"id":173,"text":"that want the United States to be embarrassed","depth":17},{"id":174,"text":"are only too happy to waive some of the technical legal rules . ''","depth":16},{"id":175,"text":"Secretary of State John Kerry particularly urged Russian authorities to work with the United States ,","depth":16},{"id":176,"text":"noting","depth":17},{"id":177,"text":"that U.S. officials have turned over seven prisoners to Russia in recent years .","depth":17},{"id":178,"text":"`` We need to cooperate on this","depth":17},{"id":179,"text":"because it 's important to the upholding of the rule of law , ''","depth":17},{"id":180,"text":"he told CNN .","depth":16},{"id":181,"text":"He defended the U.S. effort","depth":16},{"id":182,"text":"to capture Snowden for prosecution ,","depth":16},{"id":183,"text":"saying","depth":16},{"id":184,"text":"`` people may die","depth":17},{"id":185,"text":"as a consequence of what this man did . ''","depth":17},{"id":186,"text":"FBI Director Robert Mueller called his counterpart at Russia 's Federal Security Service twice Monday","depth":16},{"id":187,"text":"concerning Snowden ,","depth":16},{"id":188,"text":"a senior administration official said .","depth":15},{"id":189,"text":"And a Justice Department official told CNN","depth":16},{"id":190,"text":"that the United States is n't planning to ask for a `` red notice ''","depth":17},{"id":191,"text":"calling on members of the international police agency Interpol to take Snowden into custody","depth":17},{"id":192,"text":"-- but the official would not say","depth":16},{"id":193,"text":"whether the United States has sent or will send provisional arrest warrants to other countries","depth":17},{"id":194,"text":"that might take Snowden in","depth":18},{"id":195,"text":"or help him in his travels .","depth":18},{"id":196,"text":"It seems unlikely that Cuba , Venezuela or Ecuador","depth":16},{"id":197,"text":"-- the nations on Snowden 's potential itinerary --","depth":16},{"id":198,"text":"would be inclined to send him back to the United States .","depth":15},{"id":199,"text":"The U.S. government has already asked those three Latin American countries to not admit Snowden","depth":19},{"id":200,"text":"or to expel him","depth":20},{"id":201,"text":"if they do ,","depth":20},{"id":202,"text":"a senior Obama administration official told CNN on Sunday .","depth":18},{"id":203,"text":"But Cuba and Venezuela have long had strained relations with Washington .","depth":17},{"id":204,"text":"And Ecuador has given Assange refuge in its embassy in London for a year","depth":17},{"id":205,"text":"after he unsuccessfully fought extradition to Sweden in British courts .","depth":17},{"id":206,"text":"Assange say","depth":16},{"id":207,"text":"he fears","depth":17},{"id":208,"text":"Sweden ,","depth":19},{"id":209,"text":"which wants him","depth":20},{"id":210,"text":"for questioning about sexual assault allegations ,","depth":20},{"id":211,"text":"would transfer him to the United States .","depth":18},{"id":212,"text":"In his letter ,","depth":12},{"id":213,"text":"read by Patino ,","depth":12},{"id":214,"text":"Snowden compared himself to Pvt . Bradley Manning , the U.S. soldier","depth":12},{"id":215,"text":"accused of leaking classified information through WikiLeaks .","depth":12},{"id":216,"text":"He said","depth":12},{"id":217,"text":"U.S. officials have treated Manning inhumanely","depth":13},{"id":218,"text":"by holding him in solitary confinement ,","depth":13},{"id":219,"text":"and he predicted a similar `` cruel and unusual '' fate for himself","depth":12},{"id":220,"text":"if he falls into U.S. hands .","depth":12},{"id":221,"text":"Carney questioned Snowden 's assertion","depth":11},{"id":222,"text":"that he acted in defense of democratic transparency ,","depth":11},{"id":223,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":224,"text":"his argument `` is belied by the protectors","depth":16},{"id":225,"text":"he has potentially chosen","depth":16},{"id":226,"text":"-- China , Russia , Ecuador . '' `` His failures","depth":16},{"id":227,"text":"to criticize these regimes","depth":16},{"id":228,"text":"suggests","depth":14},{"id":229,"text":"that his true motive throughout has been to injure the national security of the United States ,","depth":14},{"id":230,"text":"not to advance Internet freedom and free speech , ''","depth":14},{"id":231,"text":"Carney told reporters .","depth":11},{"id":232,"text":"The Committee","depth":12},{"id":233,"text":"to Protect Journalists has criticized Correa 's government for pushing legislation","depth":13},{"id":234,"text":"that would roll back press freedoms ,","depth":13},{"id":235,"text":"calling its policies increasingly repressive .","depth":11},{"id":236,"text":"But Snowden is n't looking for `` political nirvana , ''","depth":12},{"id":237,"text":"said Glenn Greenwald , the columnist for the Guardian","depth":13},{"id":238,"text":"who broke Snowden 's revelations .","depth":13},{"id":239,"text":"`` He 's searching for a place","depth":13},{"id":240,"text":"where he can be safe","depth":14},{"id":241,"text":"and remain free","depth":15},{"id":242,"text":"and participate in the debate ,","depth":15},{"id":243,"text":"and Ecuador seems to be the place","depth":14},{"id":244,"text":"he has chosen , ''","depth":14},{"id":245,"text":"Greenwald told CNN 's The Lead .","depth":13},{"id":246,"text":"Carney said Monday","depth":7},{"id":247,"text":"that Hong Kong 's decision","depth":10},{"id":248,"text":"to let Snowden leave","depth":10},{"id":249,"text":"dealt efforts","depth":10},{"id":250,"text":"to build trust between the United States and China","depth":10},{"id":251,"text":"a `` serious setback . ''","depth":8},{"id":252,"text":"He declined to speculate what impact the decision could have on U.S.-China relations ,","depth":7},{"id":253,"text":"but said","depth":8},{"id":254,"text":"U.S. officials are making their displeasure known `` very directly . ''","depth":8},{"id":255,"text":"Hong Kong 's semi-autonomous government said Sunday","depth":7},{"id":256,"text":"it declined to act on a U.S. request for a provisional arrest warrant","depth":8},{"id":257,"text":"because it needed more information","depth":9},{"id":258,"text":"-- and","depth":10},{"id":259,"text":"without that information ,","depth":12},{"id":260,"text":"it said ,","depth":12},{"id":261,"text":"it had no reason","depth":12},{"id":262,"text":"to stop Snowden from boarding his flight to Moscow .","depth":12},{"id":263,"text":"Carney said","depth":8},{"id":264,"text":"U.S. officials had told Hong Kong authorities","depth":10},{"id":265,"text":"that Snowden 's passport had been revoked `` in plenty of time","depth":12},{"id":266,"text":"to have prohibited travel . '' `` We are just not buying","depth":12},{"id":267,"text":"that this was a technical decision by a Hong Kong immigration official , ''","depth":11},{"id":268,"text":"Carney said Monday .","depth":9},{"id":269,"text":"`` This was a deliberate choice by the government","depth":9},{"id":270,"text":"to release a fugitive","depth":10},{"id":271,"text":"despite a valid arrest warrant ,","depth":10},{"id":272,"text":"and that decision unquestionably has a negative impact on the U.S.-China relationship . ''","depth":8},{"id":273,"text":"But an online petition","depth":7},{"id":274,"text":"calling on the White House to pardon Snowden","depth":7},{"id":275,"text":"passed the key threshold of 100,000 signatures over the weekend","depth":7},{"id":276,"text":"and had more than 110,000 early Monday .","depth":7},{"id":277,"text":"The White House says","depth":6},{"id":278,"text":"it will respond to any petition on its site","depth":7},{"id":279,"text":"that gathers more than 100,000 signatures in 30 days .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":559,"left":0,"right":558,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":558,"left":362,"right":557,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":362,"left":331,"right":361,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":331,"left":311,"right":330,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":311,"left":287,"right":310,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":287,"left":284,"right":286,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":284,"left":282,"right":283,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":282,"left":281,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":281,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":283,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"j